@startuml Real-World Asset Tokenization Activity Diagram
title Aurigraph V11 - RWAT Asset Tokenization Workflow

|Asset Owner|
start
:Submit Asset\nTokenization Request;
note right
  Asset details:
  • Type (real estate, gold, art, etc.)
  • Value ($1M - $100M+)
  • Legal documents
  • Ownership proof
end note

:Upload Supporting\nDocuments;
note right: • Title deed\n• Appraisal report\n• Legal contracts

|Compliance Agent|
:Review Asset\nDocuments;

if (Documents Valid?) then (yes)
    :Approve Asset\nfor Tokenization;
else (no)
    :Reject Request;
    |Asset Owner|
    :Receive Rejection\nNotification;
    stop
endif

|Oracle Verification|
:Query External\nOracles;
note right
  External data sources:
  • Property registries
  • Appraisal services
  • Legal databases
  • KYC/AML providers
end note

:Verify Asset\nOwnership & Value;

if (Oracle Verification\nPassed?) then (yes)
    :Generate Verification\nProof;
else (no)
    :Escalate to Manual\nReview;
    |Compliance Agent|
    :Manual Verification;
    if (Manual Approval?) then (no)
        |Asset Owner|
        :Receive Rejection;
        stop
    else (yes)
        |Oracle Verification|
        :Override Verification;
    endif
endif

|Smart Contract|
:Deploy RWAT\nSmart Contract;
note right
  Contract parameters:
  • Token symbol: RWAT-XXXXX
  • Total supply: asset_value / token_price
  • Divisibility: 18 decimals
  • Metadata URI: IPFS hash
end note

:Mint Tokens\n(ERC-20 compatible);

|Merkle Tree|
:Generate Asset\nMerkle Proof;
note right: Cryptographic proof linking\ntoken to physical asset

:Store Proof\non-chain;

|Traceability Service|
:Link Contract\nto Asset ID;
note right
  Bidirectional mapping:
  • contract_id → asset_id
  • asset_id → contract_id
  • O(1) lookup via indexing
end note

:Create Lineage\nRecord;

|Registry Service|
:Register in RWAT\nRegistry;
note right
  Registry metadata:
  • Asset type
  • Token contract address
  • Creation timestamp
  • Owner address
  • Current valuation
end note

if (Fractional\nOwnership?) then (yes)
    |Smart Contract|
    :Enable Token\nTransfers;
    :Allow Secondary\nMarket Trading;
else (no)
    :Lock Token\nto Single Owner;
endif

|Asset Owner|
:Receive Tokenized\nAsset (RWAT tokens);

fork
    |Marketplace|
    :List on Secondary\nMarket;
    :Enable Trading;
fork again
    |Portfolio Manager|
    :Track Asset\nPerformance;
    :Monitor Valuation\nChanges;
fork again
    |Compliance Agent|
    :Schedule Periodic\nAudits;
    :Update Oracle Data;
end fork

== Ongoing Operations ==

repeat
    |Oracle Verification|
    :Periodic Oracle\nVerification (quarterly);

    if (Asset Status\nChanged?) then (yes)
        |Smart Contract|
        :Update Asset\nMetadata;
        |Merkle Tree|
        :Update Merkle\nProof;
    else (no)
        :No Action Needed;
    endif

    |Compliance Agent|
    :Compliance Check;

    if (Compliance Issue?) then (yes)
        |Smart Contract|
        :Freeze Token\nTransfers;
        |Asset Owner|
        :Notify Owner;
        :Resolve Issue;
        |Smart Contract|
        :Unfreeze Tokens;
    else (no)
        :Continue Operations;
    endif

    :Wait for Next\nAudit Cycle;
repeat while (Asset Active?) is (yes)

== Asset Redemption ==

|Asset Owner|
:Request Asset\nRedemption;

|Smart Contract|
:Burn Tokens;

|Registry Service|
:Mark Asset as\nRedeemed;

|Traceability Service|
:Archive Lineage;

|Asset Owner|
:Receive Physical\nAsset Back;

stop

note bottom
  **Key Features:**
  • Multi-oracle verification for accuracy
  • Cryptographic Merkle proofs for asset linking
  • Bidirectional traceability (contract ↔ asset)
  • Fractional ownership support
  • Secondary market liquidity
  • Periodic compliance audits
  • Immutable audit trail

  **Performance:**
  • Tokenization time: <5 minutes
  • Oracle verification: <30 seconds
  • Merkle proof generation: <1 second
  • Token minting: <10 seconds
  • Registry update: <1 second

  **Security:**
  • Quantum-resistant signatures
  • Multi-signature approval (2-of-3)
  • Role-based access control (RBAC)
  • Compliance freeze mechanism
end note

@enduml
